#### 1. Unauthenticated PII Exposure — `/users` Endpoint
**OWASP A01 (Broken Access Control) · A07 (Identification & Authentication Failures)**

The `/users` endpoint returns user names and email addresses to **any anonymous request** with no authentication or authorization check.

```js
// ❌ Current — no auth, exposes PII to the world
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    ...
  ]);
});
```

**Recommendation:** Add authentication middleware (e.g., JWT or session-based) and enforce authorization before returning user data. Email addresses are PII and should also be excluded from responses unless explicitly required.

```js
// ✅ Recommended — protect the route with auth middleware
const authenticate = require('./middleware/authenticate'); // your JWT/session check

app.get('/users', authenticate, (req, res) => {
  // Return only what the caller is authorized to see
  // Strip sensitive fields like email unless the caller has elevated privileges
