**OWASP A05 (Security Misconfiguration)**

Express serves no `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header by default, which sounds safe but means any server-side consumer can call your API. If this API is ever called from a browser, the default behavior can be silently overridden by middleware added later without a clear policy.

**Recommendation:** Define an explicit CORS policy from day one.

```bash
npm install cors
```

```js
// ✅ Recommended
const cors = require('cors');

const corsOptions = {
  origin: ['https://your-frontend.example.com'], // Allowlist specific origins
  methods: ['GET'],                               // Only permit needed methods
  allowedHeaders: ['Authorization', 'Content-Type'],
};

app.use(cors(corsOptions));
```

